{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the law for opposite-sex couples to convert civil partnership to marriage",
        "additional_details": "We believe this is unfair. Couples who wish to remain together and simply change their legal status should not be required to \u201cend\u201d their relationship in law, face long delays, or pay significantly higher costs.\r\nThis creates inequality between same-sex and opposite-sex couples and could place unnecessary emotional, legal and financial burdens on families.",
        "background": "Allow opposite-sex couples to convert civil partnerships into marriage without dissolution, Remove mandatory waiting period linked to dissolution, Introduce a simple administrative conversion process\r\nSet fees similar to those paid by same-sex couples\r\nThis would ensure equal treatment",
